<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Solving right when left is not auto on absolutely positioned non-replaced elements</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="When width and right are auto and left is not auto, the width is shrink-to-fit and then solve for right." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                position: absolute;
                left: 10px;
                right: auto;
                width: auto;
                border: solid black 1px;
                background-color: green;
            }
            p
            {
                position: absolute;
                top: 116px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div>"Shrink"</div>
        <p>The green box should be just big enough to fit the word "Shrink"</p>
    </body>
</html>